HEADWORD: Decrescendo
<hw>De`cres*cen"do</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a. & adv.</pos>
<ety>[It.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>With decreasing volume of sound;
-- a direction to performers, either written upon the staff (abbreviated
<xex>Dec</xex>., or <xex>Decresc</xex>.), or indicated by the
sign.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

